body:
@alaneckhardt, sorry for the confusion, but it looks like the changes that addressed this issue in PR #79, and those that fixed issue #78 in PR #81 ended up cancelling each other out somehow. 
After a bit of digging, I think the problem stems from including commits that manually reverted changes made by the other PR in order to split up the PRs as we discussed. 

The bottom line, however, is that neither `environment.py` nor `models.py` are currently reflecting your intended bug-fixes. If possible, could you open fresh PRs to re-close both this issue, and separately issue #78? Otherwise, I'd be happy to re-merge your fixes. I'm reopening #78, as well, and referencing this comment. Hope to get this resolved soon, and thanks again for your help!
